</div>
</p>
<p>Then for query parameters, I can say <code>$request-&gt;query-&gt;get('page')</code> and
the second argument is the default value if there is no <code>page</code> sent for
some reasons. And the same for <code>limit</code> - we'll let the client control this,
but we'll default to 5:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="c741af0fc3">
