</p>
<p>So I'm querying for all of the programmers and then slicing those down to
the ones I want. It's not an efficient way to do this, but we <em>should</em> have
a functional, paginated endpoint now. So let's try the test again, and it
works!</p>
<pre><code>php vendor/bin/behat features/api.programmer.feature:96</code></pre>
<p>Yes!</p>
<p>And to enjoy it a little bit more, we can go back to the Hal Browser, hit
Go, and since we're on page 2, we see Programmers 6-10. We can follow links
to the first page, then over to the last page to see only those 2 programmers.
Now pagination isn't hard, and it'll be really consistent across your API.</p>

    
